.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEC36D3FFB3FFB9FF7FB8FDFCEAF8BC" blockId="8.[151,1436,1494,1882]" pageId="8" pageNumber="542">
Comment: The female of this species was incorrectly interpreted by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC24B22FFB3FFB9FC03B8FDFB84F8F4" author="Snelling, R. R." box="[955,1132,1783,1809]" pageId="8" pageNumber="542" pagination="1 - 69" refId="ref6899" refString="Snelling, R. R. (1984) Studies on the taxonomy and distribution of American Centridini bees (Hymenoptera: Anthophoridae). Contributions in Science, Los Angeles County Museum of Natural History, 347, 1 - 69." type="journal article" year="1984">Snelling (1984)</bibRefCitation>
. According to the morphology he mentioned in his article, apparently he misidentified specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="4C534D50FFB3FFB9FC68B916FB14F8D0" authority="Lepeletier, 1841" authorityName="Lepeletier" authorityYear="1841" box="[976,1276,1819,1846]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="542" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="derasa">
<emphasis id="B927EAC1FFB3FFB9FC68B916FC0BF8D3" box="[976,995,1820,1846]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="542">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B927EAC1FFB3FFB9FC48B911FBD4F8D0" box="[1008,1084,1819,1845]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="542">derasa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFC24B22FFB3FFB9FBFBB911FB14F8D0" author="Lepeletier, A. L. M." box="[1091,1276,1819,1845]" pageId="8" pageNumber="542" refId="ref6239" refString="Lepeletier, A. L. M. (1841) Histoire Naturelle des Insectes. Hymenopteres. Vol. 2. Roret Paris, 680 pp." type="book" year="1841">Lepeletier, 1841</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, a species that occurs in northern South America (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC24B22FFB3FFB9FD98B935FD1EF8BC" author="Moure, J. S. &amp; Melo, G. A. R. &amp; Vivallo, F." box="[544,758,1855,1882]" pageId="8" pageNumber="542" pagination="83 - 142" refId="ref6580" refString="Moure, J. S., Melo, G. A. R. &amp; Vivallo, F. (2007) Centridini Cockerell &amp; Cockerell. In: Moure, J. S., Urban, D. &amp; Melo, G. A. R. (Eds.), Catalogue of Bees (Hymenoptera, Apoidea) in the Neotropical Region. Sociedade Brasileira de Entomologia, Curitiba, pp. 83 - 142." type="book chapter" year="2007">
Moure 
<emphasis id="B927EAC1FFB3FFB9FDCBB94AFD4CF8BC" box="[627,676,1855,1881]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="542">et al</emphasis>
., 2007
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
